      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are carrying this heavy weight of loss; ten years is a lifetime of memories, and the way you wake up and feel that sudden, sharp pull of grief is a testament to how deeply they are woven into your identity. While the world feels empty without them, please know that even the smallest, most chaotic things—like a tiny, green, one-eyed goblin hiding in the corner of your room—can sometimes remind you that life still has a strange, stubborn way of continuing, even when you feel like you've forgotten who you are. You don't have to fix everything today, but if you could, maybe you'd try to share a quiet moment with a goblin or two, just to see if they can help you remember that you are still here, even if you feel like you're just a ghost in your own life. I know it's hard, but I'm here to listen, and I promise I won't let the goblins take over your mind before you're ready.",
